cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.NE 

This paper deals with facial image analysis and machine learning techniques to discriminate between individuals with a genetic disorder and healthy individuals based on facial features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of gradient boosting and statistical analysis, which are common techniques in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves human-computer interaction, as it deals with a genetic disorder that affects communication and social interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of gradient boosting and statistical analysis to extract features and classify individuals also suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could be a possible sub-category.
